From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: tim2tox-bootstrap <bootstrap@local>
Date: Wed, 20 May 2026 07:00:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 7/7] V2TimMessage.fromJson: tolerate missing
 message_risk_type_identified

`_riskTypeIdentified` is declared as a non-nullable `int` (default 0), but
`V2TimMessage.fromJson` reads `json['message_risk_type_identified']`
directly into it without a null fallback. Any callback JSON that omits
this field (e.g. the apiCallback sendMessage success path constructed by
`MessageVectorToJsonLocal` in `ffi/dart_compat_message.cpp`) drops a
`null` into a non-nullable int slot and the immediate `> 1` comparison
on the next line throws `TypeError: type 'Null' is not a subtype of
type 'int'`.

The throw is swallowed by the outer try/catch in `_handleNativeMessage`
(lib/native_im/bindings/native_library_manager.dart) and only logged,
which silently aborts every downstream callback dispatch on that JSON
payload. Observed effects:

- Binary-replacement path: callbackType 7 (ReceiveNewMessage) never
  reaches `_advancedMessageListener.onRecvNewMessage`, so
  scenario_native_callback_dispatch_test ReceiveNewMessage subtest
  hangs to its 5s timeout.
- Platform / send path: `sendMessage` apiCallback completion never
  fires its `Completer<V2TimValueCallback<V2TimMessage>>`, hanging
  every scenario that awaits a sendMessage after friendship is up
  (scenario_multi_instance_virtual_test "Nodes can connect via
  127.0.0.1 bootstrap", scenario_friend_read_receipt_virtual_test
  "Send read receipt", etc.).

Fix: read with a null-coalescing fallback to 0 so the comparison on
the next line is always safe. This matches the declared default of
the field and the value the C++ side emits when populated.
---
 lib/models/v2_tim_message.dart | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/lib/models/v2_tim_message.dart b/lib/models/v2_tim_message.dart
--- a/lib/models/v2_tim_message.dart
+++ b/lib/models/v2_tim_message.dart
@@ -313,7 +313,7 @@
     isExcludedFromLastMessage = json['message_excluded_from_last_message'];
     isExcludedFromContentModeration = json['message_excluded_from_content_moderation'];
     customModerationConfigurationID = json['message_custom_moderation_configuration_id'];
-    _riskTypeIdentified = json['message_risk_type_identified'];
+    _riskTypeIdentified = (json['message_risk_type_identified'] as int?) ?? 0;
     hasRiskContent = _riskTypeIdentified > 1 ? true : false;
     isDisableCloudMessagePreHook = json['message_disable_cloud_message_pre_hook'];
     isDisableCloudMessagePostHook = json['message_disable_cloud_message_post_hook'];
